## Project Structure
- `src/nmon/__init__.py` — Package initialization and public API exports
- `src/nmon/main.py` — Entry point for the application
- `src/nmon/config.py` — Settings and preferences loading
- `src/nmon/db.py` — SQLite schema and database operations
- `src/nmon/gpu_monitor.py` — NVIDIA GPU metrics polling
- `src/nmon/ollama_monitor.py` — Ollama API polling
- `src/nmon/history.py` — In-memory history store and DB flushing
- `src/nmon/alerts.py` — Alert computation and state management
- `src/nmon/app.py` — Main application orchestrator
- `src/nmon/views/dashboard_view.py` — Dashboard view rendering
- `src/nmon/views/temp_view.py` — Temperature view rendering
- `src/nmon/views/power_view.py` — Power view rendering
- `src/nmon/views/llm_view.py` — LLM server view rendering
- `src/nmon/widgets/sparkline.py` — Chart rendering widget
- `src/nmon/widgets/alert_bar.py` — Alert bar rendering widget

## Data Model
- `GpuSnapshot` — GPU metrics dataclass
- `OllamaSnapshot` — Ollama metrics dataclass
- `AlertState` — Alert state dataclass
- `UserPrefs` — User preferences dataclass
- `Settings` — Application settings dataclass

## SQLite Schema
```sql
CREATE TABLE gpu_metrics (
    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    gpu_index   INTEGER NOT NULL,
    ts          REAL NOT NULL,
    temp_c      REAL,
    mem_junc_c  REAL,
    mem_used_mb REAL,
    power_w     REAL
);

CREATE TABLE ollama_metrics (
    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    ts          REAL NOT NULL,
    gpu_use_pct REAL,
    cpu_use_pct REAL,
    gpu_layers  INTEGER,
    total_layers INTEGER
);
```

## Dependencies
- `rich` — Terminal UI rendering
- `nvidia-ml-py` — GPU metrics collection
- `httpx` — HTTP client for Ollama API
- `python-dotenv` — Environment variable loading
- `pydantic-settings` — Configuration management
- `sqlite3` — Standard library for database operations
- `pytest` — Testing framework
- `pytest-asyncio` — Async testing support
- `pytest-mock` — Mocking support
- `hatchling` — Build system

## Build/Run
- `pyproject.toml` — Project configuration with build system, dependencies, and scripts
- `Architecture Plan.md` — This document
- `.env.example` — Example environment variables
- `preferences.json` — Runtime user preferences (gitignored)
- `nmon.db` — Runtime SQLite database (gitignored)

## Testing Strategy
- All modules have dedicated test files with 100% line coverage
- External dependencies are mocked using pytest fixtures
- Async functions are tested with pytest-asyncio
- Integration tests cover end-to-end functionality
- Error handling paths are explicitly tested
- All tests run with coverage target of 100%

## Design Decisions
- Use `pydantic-settings` for configuration management to provide type safety and environment variable support
- Store user preferences in JSON file for simplicity and human-editability
- Use SQLite for persistent history storage with in-memory buffers for performance
- Implement a modular view system to support keyboard-switchable dashboards
- Use rich for terminal rendering to provide a polished UI experience
- Separate alert computation from rendering to allow for different alert types
- Use a fixed-size in-memory buffer for history to balance memory usage and performance
- Implement graceful error handling with logging and fallback behavior
- Use a single entry point (`main.py`) to simplify execution and reduce complexity

